This year for Father‚Äôs Day, my family decided to really play to my dad‚Äôs Filipino roots. In traditional kamayan feasts, everyone eats off of banana leaves that have been piled high with rice, an assortment of seafood and meat, as well as vegetables. We stacked ours with sweet snow crab legs, clams, savoury clams, huge BC mussels, fresh BC oysters, BBQ‚Äôd shrimp, enoki mushrooms, steak strips, and king oyster mushrooms! The clams + mussels were cooked in two different sauces: a Corona + red Thai chili broth, and a garlic black bean paste. Scattered on top are also some of my homemade spring rolls!
